        "title": "feat(agents): add top-level subsystem logger",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds `src/agents/log.ts` exporting a `SubsystemLogger` for the `\"agents\"` subsystem\n- Follows the existing pattern of `src/agents/cli-runner/log.ts` and `src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/logger.ts`\n- Wires `agent-command.ts` as the first caller via `agentsLog.child(\"agent-command\")` — identical runtime behavior to the previous `createSubsystemLogger(\"agents/agent-command\")` call\n\n## Verification\n\nCI run [26479984925](https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/actions/runs/26479984925) on head `e8416d4a36`: `build-artifacts` ✅ `check-dependencies` ✅ `check-prod-types` ✅ `checks-node-agentic-agents` ✅\n\nLocal terminal proof (tsx v4.22.3, Node v24.15.0):\n\n```\n$ node_modules/.bin/tsx --eval \"\nimport { log } from './src/agents/log.ts';\nconsole.log('subsystem:', log.subsystem);\nconst child = log.child('agent-command');\nconsole.log('child subsystem:', child.subsystem);\nconsole.log('isEnabled(info):', log.isEnabled('info'));\n\"\nsubsystem: agents\nchild subsystem: agents/agent-command\nisEnabled(info): true\n```\n\n`log.child(\"agent-command\")` produces `\"agents/agent-command\"` — same subsystem string as the previous direct `createSubsystemLogger` call.",
